signatures.desc: Starts an unintercepted coroutine without a receiver and with result type T and executes it until its first suspension. Returns the result of the coroutine or throws its exception if it does not suspend or COROUTINE_SUSPENDED if it suspends. In the latter case, the completion continuation is invoked when the coroutine completes with a result or an exception.

signatures.text: fun <R, T> (suspend R.() -> T).startCoroutineUninterceptedOrReturn( receiver: R, completion: Continuation<T>): Any?
signatures.desc: Starts an unintercepted coroutine with receiver type R and result type T and executes it until its first suspension. Returns the result of the coroutine or throws its exception if it does not suspend or COROUTINE_SUSPENDED if it suspends. In the latter case, the completion continuation is invoked when the coroutine completes with a result or an exception.
